I found the likely root cause: during DOM compaction, duplicated AX roles like `button` are intentionally removed from the serialized attribute map to save space because the element name already implies them. The rich renderer still has `axNode.role`, but the Nano renderer only looks at flattened attributes, so it falls back to `generic`.

