Fixed the Nano ARIA regression.

Cause: `DOMStateBuilder` compacts away duplicate `role` attrs when they match the tag name, like `<button role="button">`. `DOMState.ariaSnapshot` still has AX roles, but `toNanoTree().ariaSnapshot` only saw flattened attrs, so it fell back to `generic`.

I updated `NanoAriaSnapshotRenderer` to recover implicit native roles from `nodeName`/attrs (`button`, `a[href]`, common `input` types, `textarea`, `select`, etc.) and added a regression test in `DOMStateBuilderTest`.

Verified with:

`.\mvnw.cmd -f pulsar-core\pulsar-browser\pom.xml "-Dtest=DOMStateBuilderTest#nanoAriaSnapshotPreservesImplicitSemanticRolesAfterCompaction" -D"surefire.failIfNoSpecifiedTests=false" test`

Also appended today’s daily memory and confirmed no monthly backfill was needed.


